article.headline: Green Bay 85, Detroit 74
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Rahmon Fletcher scored 24 points and Wisconsin-Green Bay defeated Detroit 85-74 Sunday. Bryquis Perine added 16 points and Alec Brown had 10 for the Phoenix (12-11, 6-5 Horizon), who pulled away late with a 9-0 run. Ray McCallum led the Titans (11-12, 5-6) with 15 points, Eli Holman had 14 and LaMarcus Lowe finished with five blocks. Both teams shot better than 50 percent, but Green Bay took advantage of 13 Detroit turnovers, turning them into 14 points. The Phoenix committed just five turnovers which resulted in four points for the Titans. Green Bay led 72-69 after Holman hit two free throws with 4:35 remaining. The Phoenix then scored on each of their next four possessions while Detroit missed its only shot in between two turnovers, making it 81-69 with 2 minutes to play. Green Bay trailed by six early but led 39-38 at halftime.
